What are some ways you took the long way round? https://t.co/RmmBYN0gLL https://t.co/Jy9JKT3USS

Everyone has their own pace. It‚Äôs easy to get caught up with how fast everyone's going. In a world of rapid growth & soft wood & fads that fade, I want to be the hard wood that is still standing in the long run! Happy, resilient, more capable of love & kindness over time.

The things that have been hardest in my life have ended up becoming the most fertile ground for my growth- often delivering  unexpected fruit. My career, our youth foundation, the mental health work are all fruits of learning to transmute pain and not rush through the process.
There is a wonderful Dine proverb: the obstacle is the path.

Do you know how hard it is to find a new style that is not contrived?! I see why so many middle aged iconic artists did tons of drugs to find freshness - cause it‚Äôs really hard to do sober!! Lol

But I think I did good üòè üòä

But you will be the judges!

So I pushed myself to find a new style that felt authentic AND felt fresh ‚Ä¶ the result is a bluesier , more soulful style of writing and singing - paying homage to hero‚Äôs of my youth like Sarah Vaughn, Etta James, Nina Simone, and Dusty Springfield.

When I sit to write I can‚Äôt really control the genre - some come out folk, some pop, some country‚Ä¶. But me being me , I didn‚Äôt want to do something I have done before

I wanted to sing in a new way
